```plantuml
@startuml elavia_edge-computing-platform-for-deep-learning-apps

actor User
participant "React Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Flask Backend" as Backend
participant "Model Manager (Go)" as ModelManager
participant "Cloud Function (TFLite Converter)" as TFLiteConverter
participant "GCS Bucket" as GCS
participant "Kubernetes Cluster" as K8s
participant "KubeEdge Node" as EdgeNode

User -> Frontend: Uploads TensorFlow Model
Frontend -> Backend: POST /api/models (with model file)
Backend -> GCS: Stores model file
Backend -> TFLiteConverter: Triggers conversion to TFLite
TFLiteConverter -> GCS: Retrieves original model
TFLiteConverter -> GCS: Stores converted TFLite model
TFLiteConverter -> Backend: Notifies conversion completion

User -> Frontend: Requests model deployment
Frontend -> Backend: POST /api/deployments
Backend -> ModelManager: Deploy model request
ModelManager -> K8s: Creates namespace/service account
ModelManager -> K8s: Deploys model service
K8s -> EdgeNode: Schedules pod with TFLite model
EdgeNode --> K8s: Pod status updates
K8s --> ModelManager: Deployment status
ModelManager --> Backend: Deployment confirmation
Backend --> Frontend: Deployment success
Frontend --> User: Shows deployment status

User -> Frontend: Requests inference
Frontend -> Backend: POST /api/inference (with input data)
Backend -> GCS: Stores input data
Backend -> K8s: Routes to model service
K8s -> EdgeNode: Executes inference on model pod
EdgeNode --> K8s: Returns inference results
K8s --> Backend: Inference response
Backend --> Frontend: Returns results
Frontend --> User: Displays results

@enduml
```